snippet: The Jets’ victory marked the official relaunch of Mark Sanchez, whose 266 yards and 3 touchdowns ended any contention that Tim Tebow will challenge him at quarterback.
abstract: Harvey Araton On Pro Football column discusses New York Jets quarterback Mark Sanchez's stellar performance during the team's 48-28 victory over the Buffalo Bills.
lead_paragraph: The Jets’ victory marked the official relaunch of Mark Sanchez, whose 266 yards and 3 touchdowns ended any contention that Tim Tebow will challenge him at quarterback.

headline.seo: Sanchez’s Performance Silences Quarterback Debate With Tebow
headline.main: Sanchez Shows There Is No Quarterback Debate
headline.print_headline: Sanchez Shows There Is No Quarterback Debate
